&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Turing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based in San Francisco, California, Turing is the world’s leading research accelerator for frontier AI labs and a trusted partner for global enterprises looking to deploy advanced AI systems. Turing accelerates frontier research with high-quality data, specialized talent, and training pipelines that advance thinking, reasoning, coding, multimodality, and STEM. For enterprises, Turing builds proprietary intelligence systems that integrate AI into mission-critical workflows, unlock transformative outcomes, and drive lasting competitive advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recognized by Forbes, The Information, and Fast Company among the world’s top innovators, Turing’s leadership team includes AI technologists from Meta, Google, Microsoft, Apple, Amazon, McKinsey, Bain, Stanford, Caltech, and MIT. Learn more at&lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--underline&quot; href=&quot;http://www.turing.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;http://www.turing.com&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;www.turing.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&quot;__next&quot; data-reactroot=&quot;&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;Job_job-details-container__9S0S3&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;Job_job-details-form-container__ReOwD&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;Section_section__S6U4V undefined&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;Job_job-details-description__cRi6W&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a skilled and dynamic Technical Program Manager to join our team. In this role, you will be responsible for identifying and addressing key business challenges, driving the product roadmap, overseeing execution, and optimizing operational processes. You will act as a bridge between technical and non-technical teams, ensuring the successful delivery of high-quality products and solutions that align with organizational goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Problem Definition &amp;amp; Analysis:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Lead the identification and definition of complex business challenges, whether they arise from delivery challenges (resource bottlenecks, technical obstacles) or customer-side issues (usability, satisfaction). Break down these challenges into smaller, manageable components and align teams toward clear goals and outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Roadmap Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Develop and maintain the product roadmap, aligning it with organizational goals. Adjust and adapt the roadmap based on changing business priorities, feedback from stakeholders, or unforeseen challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer-Centric Product Development:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Develop a deep understanding of the product’s value to customers and clients. Ensure the product addresses customer pain points and drives business growth. Ensure that features and updates meet customer expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Oversight:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Oversee the execution of operational processes, ensuring all teams are aligned and accountable for meeting program objectives. Track progress and continually optimize workflows to enhance productivity and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Management &amp;amp; Communication:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Actively manage relationships with key stakeholders, including development teams, designers, marketing, sales, customer support, and leadership. Facilitate clear and effective communication across teams to ensure alignment on goals and progress.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program Strategy &amp;amp; Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Articulate complex business problems, product strategies, and program progress to both technical and non-technical stakeholders in a clear, concise, and compelling manner. Provide regular updates on program status, roadblocks, and solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Continuous Improvement:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Proactively seek opportunities to improve the product and processes, drawing from customer feedback, performance metrics, and lessons learned. Drive ongoing optimization efforts to enhance product performance and user experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Skills &amp;amp; Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of Program Management &amp;amp; Product Management experience at a high-growth product-based startup, preferably at the intersection of technology and operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Problem Solving:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Ability to identify and analyze complex business challenges (e.g., technical, operational, or client issues) and break them into smaller, manageable problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roadmap &amp;amp; Strategic Planning:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Experience creating and maintaining a product roadmap, adjusting it based on changing priorities, feedback, and unforeseen challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Ability to build strong relationships with multiple stakeholders, including developers, designers, marketing, sales, and leadership teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Communication:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Excellent communication skills, with the ability to clearly articulate complex concepts to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Experience in overseeing the execution of operational processes and improving workflows for maximum efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management Tools:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Proficiency in using tools such as JIRA to manage tasks, track progress, and report on project status.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Analysis &amp;amp; Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Advanced skills in Excel for data analysis, reporting, and decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SQL:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Strong understanding of SQL for querying databases and analyzing data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Understanding:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Familiarity with the technical aspects of product development, including software architecture, APIs, and cloud infrastructure, to effectively communicate with development teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Values:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are client first&lt;/strong&gt;: We put our clients at the center of everything we do, because their success is the ultimate measure of our value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We work at Start-Up Speed: &lt;/strong&gt;We move fast, stay agile and favor action because momentum is the foundation of perfection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are Al forward: &lt;/strong&gt;We help our clients build the future of Al and implement it in our own roles and workflow to amplify productivity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advantages of joining Turing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Amazing work culture (Super collaborative &amp;amp; supportive work environment; 5 days a week)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Awesome colleagues (Surround yourself with top talent from Meta, Google, LinkedIn etc. as well as people with deep startup experience)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive compensation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Don’t meet every single requirement?&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Studies have shown that women and people of color are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single qualification.&amp;nbsp;Turing is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, marital status, disability, protected veteran status, or any other legally protected characteristics.&amp;nbsp;At Turing we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive and authentic workplace&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;and celebrate authenticity, so if you’re excited about this role but your past experience doesn’t align perfectly with every qualification in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyways. You may be just the right candidate for this or other roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For applicants from the European Union, please review&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.turing.com/policy&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Turing&#39;s GDPR notice here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Support Programs team is responsible for creating and executing strategies to optimize our users’ experience not only with Support, but with how they experience our Products. Stripe handles over a million support cases per year, and the Support Programs team ensures we address the highest strategic priorities to address problem areas and opportunities to provide an excellent customer experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Strategic Program Manager for Support, you will drive strategic initiatives to improve our users’ experience and our efficiency and effectiveness to serve them. Your focus areas will span user-facing lines of business such as Support, Product, and internally-focused lines of business. You will collaborate closely with Support leadership and other cross-functional leaders to inform decision-making and help shape the direction of our highest priority support initiatives, and will play a crucial role in ensuring that the team is equipped with the resources and tools necessary to deliver exceptional support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some example strategic programs include: driving the joint Support-Product strategy and operating model, improving the end-to-end experience of priority user groups (such as large platforms, AI start-ups, and Enterprises), and paid support value delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you thrive on owning an expansive and complex topic area, teasing out the highest-impact work to tackle, rallying cross-functional support, and executing against multiple workstreams in parallel to hit your objectives, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Support leadership and cross-functional stakeholders throughout Stripe to scope and execute wholly-owned large projects to address the highest priorities for the Support organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seamlessly transition from strategy to execution, by defining objectives, facilitating decision making, translating into operational plans to address key metrics, and ensuring execution and delivery against those plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate alignment, resolve ambiguity, and unblock dependencies across internal teams and cross-functional stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in strategy and operations, consulting, and/or program management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in highly cross-functional settings, and in a role that spans strategy, analysis, and operations in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong program management skills with experience managing end-to-end execution of projects/programs that have transformed their company’s operations and delivered quantifiable business impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Robust critical thinking and analytical skills, with the ability to derive strategic insights from data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the the ability to articulate complex topics in an easy-to-consume way to leaders and peers across different teams, such as product, engineering, and sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple stakeholders with varying priorities and drive creative solutions and commitment to a shared goal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with tools for tracking and reporting progress such as dashboards, project trackers, or internal documentation platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An interest in digging into the details of products and processes to improve the experience of our users and internal teams alike&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An ability to execute with minimal guidance, and in contexts with a high degree of ambiguity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in customer-facing roles (e.g. customer support, sales, partnerships, consulting, professional services, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in fintech, financial services, payments, or regulated technology environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience digging in to understand how new-to-you technical products work, and understanding customer and agent pain points&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with SQL and data analysis platforms such as Looker, Power BI, or Tableau&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;About Zipline&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Zipline is the world’s largest and most experienced drone delivery service. We are on a mission to serve all humans equally by ensuring access to food, medicine and essential goods anytime, anywhere. We design, build, and operate the world’s largest autonomous logistics system, delivering critical supplies quickly and reliably. Today, Zipline operates on four continents, makes a delivery somewhere in the world every 30 seconds, and has completed millions of deliveries to date, including blood, vaccines, medical supplies, food, and retail products.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our customers include the world’s largest and most prominent healthcare systems, governments, retailers, restaurants and global businesses who rely on us to save lives, reduce emissions, increase economic opportunity, and provide delivery from point A to point B as fast as possible. The drone is only 15% of what we’ve built to enable seamless, reliable, global operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our system strengthens supply chains, reduces congestion, and gives people time back. With more than 140 million commercial autonomous miles safely flown, Zipline is redefining access to healthcare, consumer products, and food across the globe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We operate at a global scale and are looking for practical problem solvers who thrive on real-world challenges and rapid growth. Our team is motivated by building systems that have a direct, meaningful impact on people’s lives and by scaling the future of logistics. We are seeking people who sculpt from first principles, enjoy facing adversity, and can do the impossible at record breaking speeds.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Zipline&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to change the world? Zipline is on a mission to transform the way goods move. Our aim is to solve the world’s most urgent and complex access challenges by building, manufacturing and operating the first instant delivery and logistics system that serves all humans equally, wherever they are.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From powering Rwanda’s national blood delivery network and Ghana’s COVID-19 vaccine distribution, to providing on-demand home delivery for Walmart, to enabling healthcare providers to bring care directly to U.S. homes, we are transforming the way things move for businesses, governments and consumers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The technology is complex but the idea is simple: a teleportation service that delivers what you need, when you need it. Through our technology that includes robotics and autonomy, we are decarbonizing delivery, decreasing road congestion, and reducing fossil fuel consumption and air pollution, while providing equitable access to billions of people and building a more resilient global supply chain.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You and the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Deployment, Construction, and Service Operations team has the holistic responsibility for transforming bare ground into fully operational Zipline sites. This scope spans the entire site lifecycle, encompassing design engineering, application and project engineering, construction management, site superintendents, and boots-on-the-ground technicians for installation and service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Technical Program Manager for Deployment, Construction, and Service Operations, you will drive the successful, scalable, and efficient rollout of Zipline’s global infrastructure. You will work across the entire cross-functional team—from design to field operations—to ensure that our holistic teams&#39; schedules, roadmaps, tactical execution, and strategic goals are clear, crisp, and in precise alignment with the broader organization&#39;s objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of &lt;strong&gt;process definition, systems alignment, and execution at scale&lt;/strong&gt;. You will help teams navigate complex cross-disciplinary decisions, coordinate the end-to-end site lifecycle, and ensure that our field teams have the process and technical clarity needed to deploy and maintain our infrastructure successfully worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you enjoy being &lt;strong&gt;close to the physical build-out and on the front lines of deployment&lt;/strong&gt;, working alongside engineers, construction managers, and service technicians to bring complex global systems to life, then this role will be a great fit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value people who take &lt;strong&gt;ownership of outcomes, not just responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;; you’ll be identifying systemic bottlenecks early, driving clarity for complex decisions, and ensuring work gets completed even when challenges fall outside traditional role boundaries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On any given week, you might facilitate a cross-team roadmap planning session, coordinate the rollout of a new site deployment process, or work with field teams to ensure a critical service operation is executed efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role focuses on driving clarity from ambiguity as Zipline scales, acting as the strategic architect for roadmaps that ensure the physical network scales predictably, efficiently, and reliably. The individual will navigate multiple parallel, multi-disciplinary projects across diverse domains, including global site infrastructure rollouts and continuous service improvements. You will join the organization responsible for ensuring we can rapidly and reliably transform design plans into autonomous, operational delivery sites worldwide. This position involves taking ownership of outcomes, resolving process and technical risks across the site lifecycle, and implementing foundational changes to how we deploy, build, and service our global infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Program Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Transform ambiguous goals into actionable, milestone-driven roadmaps, owning the &quot;0 to 1&quot; trajectory for poorly defined programs. Align Design, Engineering, and Service Operations to drive complex infrastructure programs from concept through real-world deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deployment and Construction Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Coordinate all aspects of prototypes, builds, and infrastructure deployments. Work across structural, electrical, manufacturing, and software domains to ensure designs translate successfully into real-world systems, capturing lessons learned for continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System-Level Technical Guidance:&lt;/strong&gt; Facilitate technical discussions, design reviews, and trade studies to help engineering teams converge on effective solutions. Guide system-level decisions across all technical domains to ensure design-to-build success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder &amp;amp; Risk Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive alignment across cross-functional leadership (Real Estate, Engineering, Construction, and Maintenance). Source and develop relationships with outside organizations, including jurisdictions, utilities, and contractors. Proactively quantify and mitigate pre-construction, construction, and operational risks, balancing urgency with cost and impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Excellence &amp;amp; Feedback Loops:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop and maintain resourcing plans for parallel projects, proactively identifying dependencies and bottlenecks. Establish mechanisms for Service Operations to feed field data back to Design, ensuring the next generation of infrastructure is designed for deployability and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clarity and Process Improvement:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop lightweight tools, documentation, and operational processes (e.g., decision logs, build playbooks) to help teams move faster and operate with clarity. Drive clear communication of program status, risks, and decisions across all stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience &amp;amp; Mindset:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6–10+ years as a Technical Program Manager (TPM) or Program Manager, delivering multi-disciplinary hardware projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with complex hardware systems (aerospace, robotics, energy, infrastructure, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operational intuition; proven success with &quot;0 to 1&quot; transitions and scaling products from prototype to global deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly execution-oriented mindset; owns outcomes and follows through relentlessly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiasm for working closely with engineers, technicians, and deployment teams on complex hardware systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical &amp;amp; Program Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to build strategic roadmaps (e.g., 5-year operating plans).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong systems thinking; able to dive into unfamiliar technical domains to guide decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in project management tools (Jira, MS Project, Smartsheet) for tracking scope, schedule, and budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Construction and Service Operations is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong systems thinking; ability to dive into unfamiliar technical domains to understand tradeoffs, guide decisions, and unblock teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience improving team effectiveness via documentation, decision tracking, or process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication &amp;amp; Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication; uses passive and active influence to drive positive change.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to coordinate cross-functional engineering teams and drive complex technical programs in fast-paced environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong facilitation skills to guide technical discussions and align diverse teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to drive complex cross-team deliveries with clear prioritization, sequencing, and risk management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and ability to influence diverse technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical, data-driven approach; comfortable defining and improving key metrics (build times, data latency, environment reliability/availability).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptability and resilience; experience introducing and scaling new processes/platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Influence Without Authority:&lt;/strong&gt; Exceptional communication skills; uses passive/active influence to drive change in challenging situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly execution-oriented; takes ownership, follows through relentlessly, and ensures details are managed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Else You Need To Know&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Zipline is an equal opportunity employer and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local laws or our own sensibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value diversity at Zipline and welcome applications from those who are traditionally underrepresented in tech. If you like the sound of this position but are not sure if you are the perfect fit, please apply!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
